<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98858240299659></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98858240299659><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=1&mid=98858240299659>soloing</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Apr 29th 6:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>LAUgh if you will but a weighted axe and a sow are your best friends to solo at higher levels i have soloed through 30 and 40 solo using this tech.  Watch the damn punny casters, why they need root to stop the target between attacks; so that they can get spells off.  Well for us the weighted axe presents the same problem a 150 delay. So run up hit target turn off attack and run when axe is ready again your attack button will light up, Turn around and hit and  so on.  I hit for min 115 to a 345 crit. not couting when i double attack. 5 or 6 hits and you turn what is chasing you.  Change back to your normal weapon for a faster kill. Note-Make sure you have a sow.  So you kiting classes kiss my barbie behind we can solo also.  By the way you can pick these axes up for 15 to 50pp.  Large races only.  Have fun kiting that delay off.  Good Luck <br><br>41 Tank<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
