	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree whith what you are saying, but there is more to being a war than AC.  <br><br>The amount of damage you do is inportant.  Damage is more about the weapon or weapons you are using, and less about str.  The more damage you do the shorter the life of the mob, the less likly the mob will argo on a healer or nuker, and the less damage you take.  <br><br>Yes you maybe out damaged by a rogue, a nuker or a monk, but you need to do enough damage so that with your taunt the mob will stick on you.  <br><br>I don't care what you have read, or what your friends say about dex.  I also play a high lvl shaman, and I know for a fact that people hit more often after I buff their dex. <br><br>One advantage of the larg races you failed to menction was slam.  Slam stuns and dose damage, this is a nice effect while fighting melee mobs, and a real advantage while fighting casters.  Nothing interurpts a spell like slam.  <br><br>The two most inportant things for a warrior?  <br>Good armor and good weapons.  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
